23:Tf67,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How much does AI call handling cost for heating engineers?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Whoza.ai starts at £59/month for the Starter plan. One captured boiler breakdown averages £120-£200 callout. A full boiler replacement can be £2,500-£4,500. At £59/month, one emergency callout pays for the whole year. Overage minutes are billed at £0.26/minute."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can Katie handle emergency boiler breakdown calls at 6am on a Sunday?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Katie answers 24/7, including weekends, bank holidays, and early mornings. She identifies emergency heating keywords like 'no heating', 'no hot water', 'boiler not working', 'leaking boiler', 'pilot light out', 'pressure dropped' — and marks the enquiry as emergency priority. You get an immediate WhatsApp with 'BOILER EMERGENCY — URGENT' in the header, even at 2am on Christmas morning."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What information does Katie collect from heating customers?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Katie collects: full name, phone number, postcode, property type (house/flat/commercial), boiler make and model (if known), fault description (no heating/no hot water/leaking/strange noise/pressure issue/pilot light), property age, whether it's a rented property, landlord details if applicable, and how they found you."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can Katie distinguish between a service call and an emergency breakdown?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Katie is trained to identify urgency from the customer's language. 'Annual service' or 'gas safety certificate' goes to routine scheduling. 'No heating', 'leaking boiler', 'strange smell', or 'pilot light keeps going out' gets emergency priority. She also asks specific diagnostic questions to help you assess urgency before you even call back."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does Katie handle landlord gas safety certificate enquiries?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Katie identifies landlord-specific calls by keywords like 'gas safety certificate', 'CP12', 'landlord', 'tenant', or 'rental property'. She captures the number of properties, number of appliances per property, preferred inspection dates, and tenant contact details. Landlord enquiries get flagged as 'landlord/multi-property' in your dashboard for efficient batch scheduling."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does whoza.ai help with annual service scheduling?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Katie captures service enquiries with full details: boiler make/model (if known), last service date, property address, preferred date range, and whether it's a single boiler or multiple appliances. She can also ask if the customer wants a recurring annual service reminder, building your repeat business pipeline automatically."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can Katie handle calls about central heating installation quotes?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Katie captures installation enquiries with: property type and size, number of radiators, current heating system (combi/system/regular/none), fuel type (gas/LPG/oil/electric), property age, budget range, and timeline. These high-value enquiries (£3,000-£8,000+) get flagged as 'installation quote' for priority follow-up."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Will customers trust an AI with their boiler emergency?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Katie introduces herself as your AI assistant and explains that she's capturing details so you can call back prepared. Most customers are relieved to speak to someone immediately rather than leaving a voicemail. In our surveys, 89% of callers are satisfied with the AI experience, and heating customers particularly appreciate that Katie captures fault details that help you diagnose before you arrive."}}]}15:["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$23"}}]
